    <abstract id="aspace_13257637fbd2c2f0e41acb60a19f8e96">John Gladstone was a member of the National Maritime Union and the Communist Party until 1949, when he was expelled from both organizations. He later became a publisher and editor at Engineer's Press, as well as an artist, and art historian. This collection includes correspondence, clippings, research notes, postcards, photographs and personal papers.</abstract>
